---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 249
Tags:
  - Combat-Action=Judgement=No Helping Friend That Day
  - 146
By: Gampopa
---
Seeing that when we die we must go on our way alone and without
kinsfolk or friends, it is useless to have devoted time (which ought
to have been dedicated to the winning of Enlightenment) to their
humouring and obliging, or in showering loving affection upon them.
